wytr.dialog.Olivin.2.1.404e5d85: Mo'in, traveller, have you heard of Corkus? The new province filled with machines!
wytr.dialog.Olivin.2.2.e678cfda: If you were level 83 I'd let you enter Corkus for free. Come back to me then!
wytr.dialog.Olivin.5.3.ad505c77: I'm not from around here. In fact I am from Corkus.
wytr.dialog.Olivin.5.4.ad5fc322: It's an independant island to the west. In fact... If you want to go...
wytr.dialog.Olivin.5.5.4528183a: We're looking for Wynn representatives. Head to the C.S.S Wavebreaker down at the dock if you want to experience Corkus. Enjoy Corkus if you go!
wytr.dialog.Olivin.2.1.26970641: The boat is down at the dock.
wytr.dialog.Olivin.2.2.49148a4d: It's really hard to miss. Just hop on!
wytr.dialog.CSSWavebreakerCaptain.5.1.a8: Welcam aboard me ship, I'll bring ye directly to Corkus.
wytr.dialog.CSSWavebreakerCaptain.5.2.56: Trust me, it is fa' more amazin than Gavel and Wynn. We even 'ave machines!
wytr.dialog.CSSWavebreakerCaptain.5.3.4e: And don't get me sterted on our architectur'!
wytr.dialog.CSSWavebreakerCaptain.5.4.ad: Trust me, you will enjoy yer stay.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.1.1.4b510458: Mo'in, Wynn traveller! Come speak to me.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.1.f860adde: It's such an honour to have a Wynn soldier visit our island.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.2.e7d57e23: We were hoping for a true envoy, but you will do.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.3.e7579149: If you follow me, I'll give you a tour of the city.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.4.89622c62: We first arrived on Corkus 350 years ago.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.1.1.5578a54d: §aHey! What are you doing back there? Follow me so I can show you the amazing Province of Corkus!
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.5.2ed4a7d5: The Corkians, like you, are from Fruma originally...
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.7.8f1bfcca: Coming from Fruma, we of course knew no magic at all.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.8.7e00651c: We soon developed our own. The rare power of
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.9.c65538f8: It's a difficult modern branch of magic that allows us to create machines.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.10.3ad3cc7: Ah, here already. Welcome to Corkus City, Capital of our island.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.11.2b5e706: We've come a long way in a short time.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.12.d88ed1b: Let me point out where the shops are.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.13.d4ffe33: North, you can buy weapons and potions. If you continue through the gate you will find the native Avos.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.14.d87133b: West, you can buy armour, and there is another entrance to the potion shop.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.15.982ca30: To the south is our bank, powder shop, scrolls, and our exclusive powder exchange!
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.16.dc7d02c: Oh! And speaking of the powder exchange, I'll start you off with some of these.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.17.6a7994a: Moving on... The south gate leads to Relos. On your way there, you might pass by the-
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.18.71a929d: Uhm, nevermind. In fact, we have a gift for you.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.19.938382c: The Five Gears Diner is hosting any guests of the island.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.20.20.b5151bb: and head to the diner for your free feast. Enjoy!
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.2.1.6588a673: We're throwing you a feast at the luxurious Five Gears Diner!
the western gate and follow the signs
wytr.text.4d940a817063d7983e49468ef64c8a: A weird sound can be heard in the distance.
wytr.narration.820275ceb50745fdb168575ad: Something is going on at the diner, you should hurry.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.4.2.ce1ce0ab: Mo'in, Wynnian. Thank goodness I stopped you!
wytr.dialog.Maxie.4.3.c4adf87c: The diner is being raided by mechs...
wytr.dialog.Maxie.4.4.f038818e: You don't know, huh? Of course you don't. Let me explain.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.1.1.86477659: The name's Maxie by the way. Nice to meet you.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.8.1.def20c6c: This town is usually full of life...
wytr.dialog.Maxie.8.3.6bbd3d17: Our own creations have rebelled against us.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.8.4.e3b99448: They now raid towns for parts.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.8.5.37b42836: Mechs are getting increasingly more desperate.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.8.6.07d93b0a: Even in rust, they are still powerful.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.8.7.ca49f685: We have tried to remove them but the factory always makes more.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.8.8.a6d41129: It is Corkus' greatest failure. It must be stopped.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.3.2.f7902f4c: I can try to open the vent to sneak in.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.3.3.f04fb098.1: Look... I know you're a stranger, but... If you want to help,
wytr.dialog.Maxie.9.2.f5993519: Alright, I'll open the door with electromagic...
wytr.dialog.Maxie.9.4.2fb27a58: Gah! I can't even do the most basic spell!
wytr.dialog.Maxie.9.7.aabb3bed: Look, I-I'm sorry for slowing you down. It's just...
wytr.dialog.Maxie.9.8.dc5d1275: Electromagic is different from your magic... And I'm not very good at it.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.9.9.8fc606a9: Oh, two paths. Well, I'm not sure which way it is, so let's split up. I'll go to the right.
wytr.text.e986ef5e015edef120a2b4ae3e4f1d: Sounds of electricity can be heard...
wytr.dialog.Maxie.10.2.017217ec: Mo'in. Sorry, had a problem with the-
wytr.dialog.Maxie.10.3.ad221c8e: ...What in the world is that mech on top of the pile of scrap over there?!
wytr.dialog.Maxie.10.4.cd3ec799: That is definitely not a regular despermech... It looks brand new!
wytr.dialog.Maxie.10.5.3b9283c1: One of those hasn't been seen since the factory was running...
wytr.dialog.Maxie.10.6.b3a3afcd: We need to do something! I'll clear the path for you. That’s the only thing I can do, I... hurt my... leg.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.10.10.c4c6d6fe.2: Meet me at the entrance where we met.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.10.10.c4c6d6fe.3: We need to report to Corkus City!
wytr.dialog.Maxie.2.1.8b83af03.1: Don't worry about the guards, they're disabled for now.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.2.2.30bfb784: I know a shortcut, we'll be in Corkus City in no time.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.9.1.a7ebb411: Mo'in! Welcome back to Corkus City.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.9.2.aec8e295: Beltrude, we have a problem! The factory is running!
wytr.dialog.Maxie.9.3.11d928c5: We saw a mech… A new mech! It looked different like it was made in-
What a load of scrap! You shouldn't talk about
wytr.dialog.Maxie.9.5.cc09d547: Our guest... just killed several despermechs by themselves.
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.9.6.48596f11: And why would we take the word of someone who can't do basic electromagic?
wytr.dialog.CorkusDelegate.9.7.e34f4722: Don't listen to Maxie. Enjoy your stay.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.9.8.aeac0f3c: They won't admit anything with you around. They want to become allies with Wynn.
wytr.dialog.Maxie.9.9.e9ecb572: Come to my house when you reach level 89, here's a key so you get in. We must prepare to break into the factory.
wytr.quest.TheHiddenCity.reward.303a: +Access to fast travel between Thesead and Eltom
wytr.quest.TheHiddenCity.reward.a85f: +Access to Juggler's fast travel to Thesead
wytr.quest.TheHiddenCity.step.87be: Talk to Narder at the Thesead Coal Mines at %s
wytr.dialog.Narder.14.1.146fa599: A human? Agh! Don't worry about getting me medical attention, I've got this under control...
wytr.dialog.Narder.14.2.241ab697: It's a broken leg. I'm already getting it treated, but I have a job to do elsewise- and a time sensitive one, too.
wytr.dialog.Narder.14.3.24a5a643: I won't be able to do it like this, but it doesn't matter if I'm the one who carries it out. It just needs to be done.
wytr.dialog.Narder.14.4.ac3783f3: I don't work for villagers, I was hired to come here by other humans... there's something you must keep secret.
wytr.dialog.Narder.14.5.9afac3d7: Swear it! If you're going to take the job, and my payment for it, you must be silent about it!
wytr.dialog.Narder.14.8.3a65491c: There is a hidden town in the canyon here. Up in the mountains- it was built and run by humans.
wytr.dialog.Narder.14.9.d85c5aaf: Now, the villagers have very strict rules about humans founding cities in their lands, and it's VERY illegal.
wytr.dialog.Narder.14.10.c72c1751: I was contacted by the Mayor because he is aware that the town may have become... compromised.
wytr.dialog.Narder.14.11.d3d906fc: The job is to figure out who and why, of course. To let this slip could collapse the treatise between our races.
wytr.dialog.Narder.14.12.9d0c79ce: I've never been to the city in the mountains, but I was given instructions. Here, I'll write down the location in your book.
wytr.dialog.Narder.14.13.dcedc5f3: Be aware though, they won't let you in unless the area is safe. They can't risk villagers wandering in.
wytr.dialog.Narder.1.1.eb7e59b9: I wrote the location of the city in your content book. There's nothing else I can do to help you.
wytr.quest.TheHiddenCity.step.f758: Head to %s to find the human town
wytr.dialog.CuriousVillager.4.1.5ff2cc52: Hm? Oh, a fellow adventurer, I see! I'm sorry, but this discovery is mine to make. There's something strange about that door...
wytr.dialog.CuriousVillager.4.2.f355bf79: Deadly gasses? Nonsense! As you can see the two of us are breathing just fine.
wytr.dialog.CuriousVillager.4.3.82ee0f64: You want me to leave? Why, so that you can have all of the glory for yourself? Ha, not a chance!
wytr.dialog.CuriousVillager.4.4.aeb3b0ef: The only way I'm leaving is if I can get that door open or if the
whole cave starts crashing down on us.
wytr.quest.TheHiddenCity.step.1424: Find a way to get the Curious Villager out of the cave
wytr.dialog.CuriousVillager.1.1.8d8fd68e: Gweh! I just had to go running my mouth about the cave collapsing! I’m out- if you have any sense you’ll leave too!
wytr.quest.TheHiddenCity.step.1094: Return to the gate and inspect the loud noise
wytr.dialog.EltomGuard.6.1.436b41cf: Thank you for getting rid of that curious villager! We thought he'd never leave.
wytr.dialog.EltomGuard.6.2.08425746: I've never seen you before. Who gave you access to the town?
wytr.dialog.EltomGuard.6.3.e6303d51: You're here in place of the detective the mayor hired?
wytr.dialog.EltomGuard.6.4.997b2890: Normally, I wouldn't believe that, but come in. We're desperate.
wytr.dialog.EltomGuard.6.5.8ffa9246: If you ever need to leave and get back, I can simply open the way.
wytr.dialog.EltomGuard.6.6.eb1512da: You probably should be going now. Our mayor can get impatient.
wytr.quest.TheHiddenCity.step.ba02: Talk to Mayor Eoric in the town hall at %s
wytr.dialog.Eoric.8.1.d852726d: What are you doing here? I'm writing an important letter, this better be worth my time.
wytr.dialog.Eoric.8.2.670fc4fa: What? Narder sent you? Why'd he send a Ragni soldier?
wytr.dialog.Eoric.8.3.3d2f76fa: I didn't think the army were authorized to know about Eltom, especially Fruma recruits.
wytr.dialog.Eoric.8.4.005b5565: Anyway, Eltom's secrecy is in great danger. We have found evidence of a traitor.
wytr.dialog.Eoric.8.5.922b3c73: We have locked down all of the exits. No one leaves or enters without my permission.
wytr.dialog.Eoric.8.6.6a99486c: We need a detective to sniff out the traitor and expose him.
wytr.dialog.Eoric.8.7.2c1e4eca: Start by asking the citizens around here about anything suspicious they've seen.
wytr.dialog.Eoric.8.8.bd540c7a: When you find the culprit, remember to leave him alive! The guards will take care of him.
wytr.quest.TheHiddenCity.step.127b: Ask Eltom Citizens about the note
wytr.dialog.Reder.1.1.acb87c03: Sorry, detective, but I haven't seen anything suspicious. In fact, I haven't even left my house for the last week.
wytr.dialog.Nichye.1.1.3414d2c6: The only suspicious thing I've seen is a hooded man walking around. There's not many people in Eltom, so it's weird.
wytr.dialog.Sybeth.1.1.7f9e3a12: If you want to find out anything, the best person to ask is Lumilda. She's in her bakery, next to the Scroll Shop.
wytr.dialog.Lumilda.6.1.66c8c040: Ah, detective! What brings you to the sweet Lumilda's Bakery?
wytr.dialog.Lumilda.6.2.f17bdeee: Hm, yes, there is a weird person coming through.
wytr.dialog.Lumilda.6.3.d6678c05: It's a hooded man. Never seen the face. A trouble maker, if you ask me!
wytr.dialog.Lumilda.6.4.1b7c4c00: He's been here a few times, usually writing things on a piece of paper. That man's a real mystery. No one even knows where he lives.
wytr.dialog.Lumilda.6.5.41b3ceab: One time my grandson couldn't resist and followed the man. Last thing he saw was the man leaving through the Eastern Exit.
wytr.dialog.Lumilda.6.6.2869396b: Ain't that a place to start, sweetheart?
wytr.quest.TheHiddenCity.step.0cd7: Inspect anything beyond the Eastern Exit at %s
wytr.text.9a3b45c2f616dc248ff203194cb03c: There appears to be a cave up above.
wytr.dialog.???.6.1.bb963763: Ah, you must be the detective. None of those half-witted Eltomites could figure it out.
wytr.dialog.???.6.2.40ed56d9: I guess the grook is out of the pen then.
wytr.dialog.???.6.3.6e28b740: This town shouldn't even be here. Humans aren't allowed to own land in Gavel like this.
wytr.dialog.???.6.4.3ccf5a29: These humans couldn't be bothered to fight their own war, so they hid an entire city here.
wytr.dialog.???.6.5.573b22fa: Traitor? I'm no traitor. I'm just looking to carry out the law where it needs to be carried out. Nothing personal, yes?
wytr.dialog.Ardulf.6.6.665ee04b: Maybe they'll actually use “Ardulf” instead of saying “freak” once they've seen the good I can do for them!
wytr.quest.TheHiddenCity.step.ba09: Look for clues in Ardulf's house
wytr.narration.76e995411dc2064b732cb9a34: - Mayor's office on the top layer of Thesead
wytr.narration.523527dfe8bfff8d08a844466: - Remember to set up Dwarven bank account
wytr.narration.5f57777a93bb0f5d2d9a7c7de: It's Ardulf's notes. Doesn't seem like there's anything else to them...
wytr.narration.42dba7730144d9c9aa85b59f8: Rifling through the papers doesn't reveal any other plans, but there's a letter buried in the stack.
wytr.narration.34663d46b08bad94d4606cbfd: Most of the text seems to be completely illegible, and it's covered in hoof-prints?
wytr.narration.0ecbacf849078253fc9e203fb: The letter is signed with an excessively flowery signature completely at odds with the rest- It's so ornate that the only letter you can actually make out is a D.
wytr.narration.e1e1c3e7c3055f363843195f8: There also seems to be a subscription to some kind of monthly picture-painting service enclosed...
wytr.narration.5205f89242d4e54e981f328dd: All it offers is various paintings of plain cows with muscular bodies crudely scribbled onto them. The subscription hasn't been filled out.
wytr.dialog.Hilan.5.3.0f2952ed: Demanded to use a ship... I refused...
wytr.dialog.Hilan.5.4.d23aac08: He beat me up... And left...
wytr.quest.TheHiddenCity.step.a553: Head up the Airbase's Tower to confront the hooded man
wytr.text.0a810bd680e37233a29d12fdef7ef1: You feel a heavy blow to the back of your head.
wytr.dialog.Ardulf.4.1.cf97123b: What are you doing here? Why are you protecting this illegal town?
wytr.dialog.Ardulf.4.2.f3c96ae2: The Villagers will not be happy about Eltom. This could seriously harm the Gavel-Wynn relationship.
wytr.dialog.Ardulf.4.3.60d1aedb: You can't stop me. You wouldn't murder one of your own, would you?
wytr.dialog.Ardulf.4.4.ca2fb375: I will tell the mayor of Thesead all about this place, and claim my reward for doing so. I will be rich and if you want to stop me you'll have to do it yourself.
wytr.text.26629646db8632571a1bad61b899e3: ...you got snuck up on and knocked out. Where are you now?
wytr.quest.TheHiddenCity.step.0124: Escape your cell and find a way to sabotage the ship
wytr.text.40892dad9df8017a22b43f2f7ab40b: To escape your cell you must pick this weird lock. It seems that spinning a ring will spin the rings next to it the other way.
wytr.narration.5a6b8d259461a58cd0b378fce: The ship you're running is a mess. This is the third time I've had to repair a coolant leak here.
wytr.narration.d7879af9caaec250720789833: The Corkian machines are great, but they aren't eternal. At this rate, you'll need a new ship every winter.
wytr.narration.d8886539f1fd4391ea070b59e: Is it that hard to understand that
no liquid should enter the engine?
wytr.inform.ffd49b2dc6c3: §e[!] §cEngine breakdown detected! Cargo hold opened for emergency repairs!
wytr.quest.TheHiddenCity.step.1b2d: Talk to Thesead's Mayor at %s at the top of Thesead
wytr.dialog.TheseadsMayor.7.1.4fd14cf7: What brings a human to my office?
wytr.dialog.TheseadsMayor.7.2.851c4f56: A letter? Oh, that. The one about Eltom? Don't look so worried. The secret is safe with me.
wytr.dialog.TheseadsMayor.7.3.2eacc324: Yes, I know about Eltom. After all, its mayor is my ex-husband.
wytr.dialog.TheseadsMayor.7.4.ffdc7cba: It may seem odd, a love between a villager and a human. I know, but our race did not stop us from being in love.
wytr.dialog.TheseadsMayor.7.5.90b2d10a: The person who left the letter about Eltom is our son, Ardulf. As soon as Eoric found out about our child, he panicked and left me.
wytr.dialog.TheseadsMayor.7.6.e5bec978: Ardulf will never be accepted as a half breed... Still, I hope he's OK.
wytr.dialog.TheseadsMayor.7.7.0f250491: Huh, oh yeah, one more thing. The switch under the table... go on, press it!
wytr.dialog.TheseadsMayor.1.1.2cb0699f: Let's keep what happened here a secret, okay?
wytr.dialog.Eoric.1.1.e7911303: Eltom and its citizens are thankful for your service. The line between Human and Villager remains firmly in place... For the most part.
wytr.dialog.Hilan.1.1.b0085046: Thank you for chasing down that odd looking man, he really injured me. If I was a villager, I'd be suing someone!
wytr.narration.d9e4b61624e62a33fce1ead20: Day 1 -- I've just arrived in this remote place. No signs of life so far. Finding this treasure should be easy.
wytr.narration.50e30d3244c1092030a30e964: Day 4 -- While looking for the treasure I encountered what looks to be an orcish camp. I didn't see any orcs though, but for now I will keep my distance.
wytr.narration.1f7a32646e92e01445544acee: Day 8 -- I decided to check up on the camp. No orcs to be seen anywhere. I can explore the western part of the valley safely.
wytr.narration.e15515ba6dbc4a51c9a4addfc: Day 15 -- There is nothing in the lower part of the valley. Perhaps the treasure isn't real?
wytr.narration.15f64bdd4c422859dc84a5fde: Day 16 -- Success! I might've found a lead to the treasure. Under the river there was a chest with a note inside of it. The note points to an area by the big, smoking volcano. That must be it. I know it!
wytr.narration.b4aef47614c7922e84ef45a98: Day 17 -- Today it the big day. I am headed to the volcano right now with my mining equipment. Who knows, maybe the cave where the treasure is has caved in?
wytr.narration.30e4ae2bc9cf1ed330980a1f7: Day 20 -- Looks like the cave has indeed caved in. I've been clearing out the stones for three days straight with no sign of a treasure. But I will not give up. The treasure is somewhere here. It is.
wytr.narration.435a3495a98a8db166fea2dbd: Day 25 -- Eight days of digging and I hit a wall of bedrock. There is no way the treasure was in that cave. Maybe the note was there to mislead me? I'll have a look at the valley once more to see if I can find the treasure.
wytr.narration.a4afb1918a9bbfabc1b4d0f43: Day 28 -- I've turned the whole place upside-down and the most valuable thing I've found is a spear from the orcish camp. I didn't fake my death for this!
wytr.narration.f6d87f90e47f79820e8818187: Day 30 -- Maybe someone else took the treasure? Clearly, someone else has been here before me. Who built these bridges? They didn't just pop out of nowhere! Maybe they didn't find the treasure? Maybe they didn't because it wasn't there?
wytr.narration.c908e8705f0fe554c87512591: Day 34 -- I'm going stir-crazy. The food supply is low. My last hope is a gulch I can barely see...I'll have to climb it to escape. There is no treasure here, for certain!
wytr.narration.617755e185ca109f3d015e342: handwriting is different on this next page.
wytr.narration.998d3d21c6b3883ca70bbbef9: The fool wandered into the inescapable gulches of this canyon. We empty husks preside over it, banished here by the very sorceror we sought to eliminate.
wytr.narration.e4498e09771a2d43f3e18f063: He met his fate through a simple slip. We saw it all- and we find this is as far as we can go. The sorceror's spell prevents our movement further.
wytr.narration.1aa4ef3455002eba821dd8a7c: His ranks join ours, the lost heroes, whose lives were stripped away and whose work has tarnished with needless bloodshed. To any who should venture here...
wytr.narration.a5a01208fb283489ecdbe1583: We have pushed forward a cannon. It is the only escape we can provide from our eternal outpost. If you use it, however, you must take a vow to us.
wytr.narration.9fbf8c9252afe3e6f1b398aed: Dismantle the corrupt Guilds that plague this land. They no longer protect the land as they ought once have done. Fight till your last breath to return them to their former glory.
wytr.narration.f32362e7f86c29ba28653ac84: The rest of the pages are blank... Who wrote this?
